  "flow": {
    "mermaid": "sequenceDiagram\n  participant Client\n  participant Gateway as API Gateway\n  participant PetResource as PetResource\n  participant OwnerRepo as OwnerRepository\n  participant PetRepo as PetRepository\n  participant DB as Database\n\n  Client->>Gateway: POST /api/customer/owners/{ownerId}/pets\n  Gateway->>PetResource: POST /owners/{ownerId}/pets (lb)\n  PetResource->>OwnerRepo: findById(ownerId)\n  OwnerRepo->>DB: SELECT * FROM owners WHERE id = ownerId\n  DB-->>OwnerRepo: Owner row\n  OwnerRepo-->>PetResource: Owner entity\n  alt Owner not found\n    PetResource-->>Client: 404 ResourceNotFoundException\n  end\n  PetResource->>PetRepo: findPetTypeById(petRequest.typeId)\n  PetRepo->>DB: SELECT * FROM types WHERE id = typeId\n  DB-->>PetRepo: PetType row\n  PetRepo-->>PetResource: PetType entity\n  PetResource->>PetResource: new Pet(name, birthDate, type, owner)\n  PetResource->>PetRepo: save(pet)\n  PetRepo->>DB: INSERT INTO pets (name, birth_date, type_id, owner_id)\n  DB-->>PetRepo: saved Pet\n  PetRepo-->>PetResource: Pet entity\n  PetResource->>PetResource: wrap as PetDetails\n  PetResource-->>Gateway: 201 PetDetails JSON\n  Gateway-->>Client: 201 PetDetails JSON",
    "narrative": "A client POSTs a PetRequest (name, birthDate, typeId) to the API Gateway, which routes it via load-balanced HTTP to PetResource.processCreationForm in the customers-service. PetResource first fetches the Owner by ownerId through OwnerRepository; if not found, ResourceNotFoundException returns a 404. It then resolves the PetType via PetRepository, constructs a new Pet entity linked to that owner, and persists it with a database INSERT. The saved Pet is wrapped into a PetDetails response and returned as HTTP 201.",
